==French, Japanese, Portugeese, Dutch==
===Noun===
'''bonbon''' ''m'' (plural: [[bonbons]], diminutive: [[bonbonnetje]])

A round, chocolate-covered wafer. On the inside are usually bits of coconut or melted milk chocolate. They are sometimes hard to find. Often come in other flavors such as toffee, strawberry, or mint.

